{
  "doc_id": "39505",
  "text": "All the procedures described above require synergetic operation of several different components of the scanner, such as RF amplifiers, gradient amplifiers, and analog-to-digital converters with precise timing. An embedded computer that runs a realtime operating system implements desired actions. By the fact that different devices, electronic systems, sensors, mechanical parts (the subject is introduced to the scanner using a moving table), computers, and software are integrated under a single roof, the MRI scanner is a mechatronic system [10] , [CITATION_1] .",
